post_text: The MT varsity football team is hosting the Mustangs of Westfall in a pre-season scrimmage tomorrow night at 7pm. Due to COVID-19 restrictions, the scrimmage is NOT open to the public. Limited attendance is permitted under the newly issued Ohio Department of Health orders, primarily to immediate family members (4). While we understand the disappointment of many in not being able to attend in person, we will be live-streaming the scrimmage beginning at 6:55pm. Please check back to the district facebook page for the link to the streaming service. While times are different and things can not be like they have always been, we ask that you be understanding and respectful as we follow the guidelines given to us. Go Panthers!!!

Parents/Guardians,
Following this afternoon's meeting with the Fayette County Health Department, a return in Plan A -Traditional Setting- is still being supported for students at Miami Trace. We appreciate the cooperation and partnership with our local health department.

Please understand, conditions change daily, so it is very important to check your email along with our district website and social media pages. Miami Trace adopted a Restart Plan Guidance Document on July 13, that includes multiple learning plans, and we must be ready to use any of them (Plan A- B- or C) at any point in the future should conditions change.

Just a reminder, please make sure you have completed the InfoSnap re-registration for your child(ren). This needs to be submitted before a student receives a technology device.

Thank you for your continued understanding during this time.

Miami Trace has launched the special online learning option for those families who are not comfortable with an in-person return to campus for the 2020-2021 school year.

This online learning opportunity is known as the Panther Virtual Academy, and it serves Miami Trace students in grades K-12.

Registration for Panther Virtual Academy will open on Tuesday, July 21st, and can be completed under the Students & Parents tab on the Miami Trace website.

Deadline for registration is Friday, August 7th.

If you have specific questions prior to registering, please contact your child's school building or the central office.

https://www.miamitrace.k12.oh.us/StudentRegistration.aspx

A message from new superintendent Kim Pittser

It is a privilege to serve as the new superintendent of Miami Trace School District. I want to thank the MT Board of Education for having the confidence in me to lead our district. I look forward to continuing work with our staff, students, and community.
The past 20 years of my time in education have been spent as a Panther, and I am grateful for the experience gained and relationships built. We have a tremendous staff that shares a student-centered philosophy and acknowledges our responsibility to our taxpayers and stakeholders. Together, we will make advancements and support our students to reach their fullest potential.
MT PROUD!

post_text:
Message from Superintendent
David Lewis

Good afternoon. On Thursday evening I verbally agreed to become the new superintendent of the Newark City School District. This is a bittersweet moment for me. I am excited for a new opportunity, yet sad to be leaving such a special place.

I will be forever grateful for the opportunity to serve as the superintendent of this district for the past seven years. Miami Trace will always hold a special place in my heart. I have made many memories and friends that will last a lifetime.

Over the past seven years I have attended many contests, activities, and events in this district. I can honestly say that I have never been disappointed in the way our students have conducted themselves. They always represent Miami Trace with class. This is a tribute to the families and staff that work with our students everyday.

The future for Miami Trace is bright, and I will remain one of the biggest fans. Thank you for making my family and I feel at home for the last seven years. Go Panthers!

post_text:
Sixth Grade Band
DON'T MISS OUT! THE TIME IS NOW!

The 6th graders finally have the opportunity to do what so many have done before them, be a part of the band! The journey begins in 6th grade and each year more opportunities for band students are presented. Various contests and events are available in middle school as well as a Trills and Thrills Contest trip to Kings Island for 8th graders. Once a student reaches high school they have the opportunity to be involved in a number of bands including Symphonic Band, Concert Band, Jazz Band, Marching Band, and Pep Band. The journey begins now!

If you have a child entering the 6th grade for the 2020-2021 school year and would like more information on the band program, please email Miss Evans at tevans@mtpanthers.org for more information!

Good evening. In response to the confusion surrounding graduation ceremonies this spring, the Ohio Department of Education and Ohio Department of Health released updated guidelines this afternoon. With this information, we will be moving forward with our hybrid/virtual ceremony. Mr. Enochs will be sending detailed information to each senior and his or her parents tomorrow. Please see the link below for the complete statement.

Our hearts go out to our seniors during this time. We understand the disappointment this announcement will cause, but remain committed to giving our seniors the best possible experience under the current circumstances. We greatly appreciate your support and understanding. Thank you.

David L Lewis
Superintendent

2020 MIAMI TRACE HS GRADUATION

In response to the order from the Ohio Department of Health, guidance from Governor DeWine, and the Ohio Department of Education, Miami Trace will not hold a traditional graduation ceremony for the class of 2020. This difficult decision was made in consultation with our local authorities and was not taken lightly. We are committed to recognizing our graduating seniors in a manner that honors each student in a safe and responsible way, while prioritizing the health needs of students, their families and the community. We share in the disappointment for our seniors, but believe we have developed a hybrid graduation ceremony that will honor them in a special way‚Ä¶ More

There have been questions pertaining to the school calendar in response to the government shutdown for the remainder of the 19-20 school year. All distance learning activities and instruction will continue until May 15. This will remain the date for the last official day of school. If you have specific questions, please reach out to your child's teacher or principal.

The final day for the food service program will be Tuesday, May 12.

Thank you and have a great weekend!

Miami Trace High School Cancels Production of Footloose Over COVID-19 Pandemic

In response to recent events‚Äîand in the best interest of our cast, crew, and audience members‚Äîwe have decided to cancel all full performances of ‚ÄúFootloose.‚Äù It is our hope that at some point we will be able to have an abbreviated performance that would feature the musical selections in the show.

If you have purchased tickets, you have two options. The first option is a full refund. If you require a refund, you can email tickets@showtix4u.com with a refund request for the face value of your ticket. **fees are non-refundable. The second option is to donate the money to the vocal music program. If you would like to offer your purchase a donation, no further action is needed. We appreciate all of your support, and we hope to see you at future Miami Trace High School productions.

post_text:
Good afternoon. As you know, Governor Dewine extended the closure of all K-12 schools through May 1. With the daily number of COVID-19 cases on the rise, we are doing our best to limit exposure for both MT staff and community members. As a result, the following changes are being made to the meal service program from April 6 - May 1:

- Monday will be used for meal prep and organization.
- Meals will be distributed to students every Tuesday from 11-1.
- Students will receive 5 breakfasts and 5 lunches.
- The only location being used for meal distribution is the football stadium parking lot.
- The location will be set up as a drive-thru, so nobody has to leave their vehicle.
- Students do not need to be present to receive meals, but names must be given to district personnel for documentation.

We greatly appreciate your continued support during these challenging times. Thank you!

post_text: On Saturday, February 22nd 2020, Miami Trace High School freshman class officers, delivered donations to the Fayette County Humane Society. These donations were collected over the course of two weeks. President Jacob Cline thought of this community service project. The donations added up to the amount of 32 items. Since the Fayette County Humane Society is always in need of supplies like food, treats, and toys, asking the Miami Trace freshmen class to bring in these items was an easy way to help supply these donations. Class Vice President Sara Dawson helped with supplying information about this project. She has donated to the humane society in the past by giving blankets and other supplies.‚Ä¶ More

post_text:
The Miami Trace Local School District is currently experiencing a high volume of influenza B cases throughout the district. Over the past several days, we have worked closely with the Fayette County Health Department to monitor the situation. As a result, the district will be closed on Friday, January 17, 2020. This will provide four days and the opportunity to thoroughly disinfect our facilities and buses.

As a precautionary measure, the entire district will be shut down until the start of the school day on Tuesday, January 21, 2020. All district activities and contests will be canceled this weekend, including youth programs. We ask that everyone please stay out of the school buildings over the weekend. We greatly appreciate your support and cooperation. The wellness and safety of our students will always be our number one priority at Miami Trace. Thank you.
